title: Wallabies make emphatic case for the defence
text:
Wallabies 15 Wales 6 match report: Australia top Pool A with backs-against-the-walls Twickenham win IAIN PAYTEN in London The Daily Telegraph Wallabies 15 Wales 6 match report: Australia top Pool A with backs-against-the-walls Twickenham win IAIN PAYTEN in London The Daily Telegraph Wallabies overcome all odds with huge defensive effort 1:13 
Rugby World Cup: The Wallabies have overcome all odds including two yellow cards, missing starters and injuries to key players to defeat Wales in their Pool A World Cup match. October 11th 2015 12 hours ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/Rugby Union/Rugby World Cup/ 
THE Wallabies held Wales out for seven minutes with 13 men in a spectacularly courageous defensive effort to win a tryless clash at Twickenham and book a quarter-final date with Scotland. 
It was a defensive performance that will go down in World Cup history but injuries to key players took some of the shine off.
